    "The challenge is exacerbated by the frequent use of colloquialisms and new terms on Chinese social media platforms like Chinese Weibo, which are not always captured by traditional rule templates.",
    "As shown in Fig. 2, the \"rule-based\" keyword appears in the C3 community.",
    "This reflects the close relationship between rule-based methods and machine learning approaches in Chinese sentiment analysis.",
    "To overcome the limitations inherent in rule-based methods, these techniques are often combined with machine learning or deep learning methods to enhance the accuracy and robustness of Chinese sentiment analysis (Wen and Li 2014; Yan et al. 2018).",
    "As more and more users or consumers express their opinions and experiences about products or services online, a large number of comments or opinion texts are in urgent need of sentiment analysis and mining (Zhang et al. 2011; Wang et al. 2014b)."
